g went wrong. You\u2019re all set! We\u2019ll let you know when Novi is available. Frequently Asked Questions When will Novi be available? Novi is currently being built. Sign up here to be one of the first to know about Novi. What do I need to get started? When Novi is available, you will need a government-issued ID to sign up for an account. Identity verification is important to comply with laws and prevent fraud, so you know people are who they say they are. How can I use Novi? Novi will be available as a stand-alone app in the App Store and Google Play. You will also be able to use Novi directly in your WhatsApp and Messenger apps, so you can send and receive money as easily as you message friends, family, and businesses. What can I use Novi for? Novi is designed for the Libra payment system. You can use Novi to send money around the world. You can also keep Libra digital currencies in your Novi wallet and use it to pay for everyday transactions wherever it is accepted. Will Novi charge fees? What you send is what they get. You can add, send, receive, and withdraw money from your wallet without worrying about hidden charges. Novi is cutting fees to help people keep more of their money. Where is Novi available? Our goal is to make Novi available to everyone, anywhere in the world. We\u2019re working to bring Novi to as many countries as possible, as soon as the Libra network is available. Can I use my local currency in Novi? Novi is designed for the Libra payment system, so when you send and spend your money, you\u2019ll be using Libra digital currencies. Through Novi, you can use your local currency to purchase Libra, and also convert Libra back to your local currency when you want to withdraw. How will you prevent fraud? Accounts and transactions are verified, and fraud prevention is built in throughout the app. Novi uses government-issued IDs to verify customers, so you can trust people are who they say they are. Novi also has in-app reporting and dedicated customer care. In the event of fraud, you will be eligible to receive a full refund. How will Novi keep my information safe? Your Novi transaction history will only be visible to you. To read more about how we are protecting your data, click here. Can I still use Novi if I don\u2019t have a Facebook, WhatsApp, or Messenger account? Yes. Novi will also be available as a stand-alone app that does not require you to have a Facebook, WhatsApp, or Messenger account \u2014 you just need a government-issued ID to sign up. What\u2019s the relationship between Novi and Facebook? Novi Financial, a regulated financial company, is a subsidiary of Facebook, Inc. and is headquartered in Menlo Park, California. Can businesses use Novi? Novi will support peer-to-peer payments. Over time, additional merchant services will help businesses big and small accept Libra online, in-app, and in-store. What is the Libra payment system? The Libra payment system incorporates three elements that work together to create a more inclusive financial system: (1) A secure, scalable, and reliable blockchain as the technological backbone of the payment system; (2) Libra digital currencies that are backed by a reserve of assets made up of cash and short-term government securities; and (3) Governance by the Libra Association, an independent membership organization tasked with developing and operating the Libra payment system. Novi Financial is one Member of the Libra Association. What are the digital currencies supported by the Libra payment system? Initially, the Libra payment system will support only a few digital currencies, such as ??????????????????USD, ??????????????????GBP and ??????????????????EUR, which will have the same value in the country\u2019s respective currency (e.g. 1 USD, 1 GBP, 1 EUR). The Libra payment system will also support a combination of these digital currencies, ??????????????????LBR. Over time, the Libra payment system intends to support additional digital currencies. AboutNewsC